description: This is the data dictionary for the Sentinel Data Quality Assurance and Characterization Program Package. This includes data dictionaries for the program package input file datasets and datasets output to the msoc and dplocal subdirectories.

inputfiles.name: inputfiles
inputfiles.description: Input files are used to parameterize the program.

datasets.description: This table is used by the control flow module to selectively and sequentially execute QA modules. It is also used in the L1 and L2 modules to selectively execute data checks by SCDM table. This table contains one row per QA package integrated module, excluding any 'add-on' stand-alone programs---e.g., Mother-Infant Identification.

variables.description: Abbreviated name of the module to be executed.
Indicates whether the specific module will be executed.

values.value_map: Yes. The module will be executed.
No. The module will not be executed.

variables.description: Full name of the SAS program module. Case sensitive and should contain no spaces or special characters except `.`, `_`, or `-`.
Common Components (CC) macro variable used by all modules, including the QA package master program. Used to provide DP and ETL-specific SCDM table names to the QA package.

datasets.description: This SAS output table provides a list of SOC-assigned error codes (FlagID) and descriptions (Flag_Descr), and the name of the output dataset used to evaluate checks associated with the error code.

variables.description: A unique error code representing an individual data check.
Indicator for implication of the data check for passing or failing an ETL under review.

values.value_map: The ETL cannot pass QA review until fixed.
The ETL may be able pass QA review, pending Quality Assurance Analyst Review.
This flag is for characterization or reference purposes. It does not generally affect the ability of the ETL to pass QA review.

variables.description: Indicator for implication of the data check for the QA package. AbortYN = `Y` is used to indicate checks that must pass in order to complete the QA module successfully.

values.value_map: Yes. The QA Package will abort if this flag is present.
No. The QA Package will not abort if this flag is present.
